<SLUG> BC-BKN-CLIPPERS-NOTES-LBPT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BLOWING THE WHISTLE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RANDY HILL  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The Clippers don't exactly require assistance in
the art of losing, but plenty of NBA employees keep volunteering to
help.
</P>
<P>
   Exhibit Z was Friday's loss to the SuperSoncis in Seattle, where
the home team attempted 36 free throws, while the Clippers squeezed
off 14.
</P>
<P>
   At halftime, the count was 11-10, Sonics, but the zebras gave a
clutch performance down the stretch.
</P>
<P>
   One non-call that was of grim fourth-quarter consequence to the
Clippers involved point guard Darrick Martin, whose arm was whacked
by Seattle All-Star Gary Payton. The ball went out of bounds, but
was awarded to Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   Martin took the high road when the subject was brought up before
Saturday's game vs. Utah at The Pond.
</P>
<P>
   ``We need to make some plays so we don't leave it (outcome) in
somebody's else's hands,'' Martin said of the less-than-friendly
whistles.
</P>
<P>
   subhead Sore points
</P>
<P>
   Martin, who hyperextended his left knee in Wednesday's loss to
Golden State, played 31 minutes Friday in Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm still about 80 percent,'' he said, referring to the knee.
</P>
<P>
   His backup du jour is Troy Hudson, who - including the Jazz game
-is three games into a post-CBA, 10-day contract.
</P>
<P>
   Hudson played 17 minutes in Seattle, and scored five points
before fouling out in the fourth quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Last season, his first after leaving Southern Illinois following
his junior season, he played eight games for the Jazz while John
Stockton was out.
</P>
<P>
   ``I learned a lot playing against Stockton while I was there,''
said Hudson, whose education was accelerated by Payton on Friday.
``He's very aggressive and really smart.''
</P>
<P>
   Veteran point guard Pooh Richardson is scheduled to bring his
tender ankle off the injured list for Monday's game in Denver. Yet
another injured point guard, Sherman Douglas (thigh), is required
to spend two more games on the shelf.
</P>
<P>
   Subhead Forwards backward
</P>
<P>
   Forward Rodney Rogers missed Saturday's game with a contusion of
the right knee he acquired against Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   Forward Maurice Taylor rolled his right ankle in the same game,
but returned and finished with 11 points.
</P>
<P>
   Taylor remained a bit gimpy Saturday, but was in the lineup
against Utah.
</P>
</TEXT>
