<HEADLINE>
THIS TIME, SHAQ'S JABS HIT EWING
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Shaquille O'Neal's rotating rivalry _ he's gone
through David Robinson, Tim Duncan, Greg Ostertag and Olden
Polynice _ lands today on Patrick Ewing. O'Neal's pro wrestling
bravado was aimed at the Knicks' center in a Sports Illustrated
article published last week.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's somebody I really don't like, especially since the
lockout,'' O'Neal said of Ewing, the players union president. ``Let
me tell you this: Patrick and his Georgetown boys messed up the
lockout. Georgetown is supposed to be a five-star university? Yeah,
right. That's why he and Zo (Alonzo Mourning) were trying to play
lawyer, trying to intimidate billionaires like (Portland owner)
Paul Allen. Please.''
</P>
<P>
   Ewing's response? ``I'll see him on Sunday.''
</P>
<P>
   As the Lakers prepared for the Knicks, O'Neal said he's not
concerned about firing up Ewing.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'll just do what I do to all the other big men, play hard and
whoop their (butts). If he comes with extra, then I come with
extra,'' he said. ``Let me tell you something, no human can break
me down. If he wants to fight, we can fight. If he wants to go to
war, we can just go to war. I back down to no man. He puts his
drawers on the same way I put my damn Calvin Klein drawers on.''
</P>
<P>
   Big bench: Overshadowed in Friday's loss to Sacramento was one
of the best performances of the season from the Lakers' reserves.
In fact, it was almost entirely bench players who built the
double-digit first-half lead that was later squandered in the third
quarter by the starters.
</P>
<P>
   Rick Fox, J.R. Reid, Derek Fisher and Robert Horry entered the
game late in the first quarter, joining starter Kobe Bryant, and
the group scored 20 points in four minutes to take a 30-20 lead by
the end of the period.
</P>
<P>
   Fox and Fisher each sunk a pair of 3-pointers in the run for 12
quick points, while Bryant added seven. Defensively, Fox, Horry and
Bryant all blocked shot attempts, and Fisher added a steal.
</P>
<P>
   For the game, the bench finished with 27 points (13 from Fox),
20 of the Lakers' 42 rebounds and 12 assists.
</P>
<P>
   Missing: Dennis Rodman wasn't the only Laker missing from
Saturday's practice. Backup center Sean Rooks, who hasn't played
the last two games, was excused from practice to attend to personal
matters, according to the team.
</P>
</TEXT>
